## âš¡ What is DeepDrift?

Traditional AI monitoring looks at **inputs** (data drift) or **outputs** (confidence, perplexity).  
**DeepDrift looks inside the model itself.**

Think of it as an **MRI for neural networks**.

DeepDrift measures **Semantic Velocity** â€” the rate of change of hidden representations â€” and uses it as a real-time stability signal.  
It functions like a **â€œCheck Engineâ€ light** for AI systems.

| Domain | Failure Mode | DeepDrift Diagnosis |
|------|-------------|--------------------|
| ğŸ‘ï¸ Vision | OOD / geometric stress | **Global Collapse**, **Avalanche Effect** |
| ğŸ—£ï¸ LLMs | Confident hallucinations | **Semantic Tremor** (7â€“8 tokens early) |
| ğŸ¤– RL / Robotics | Silent policy failure | **Panic Zone** (seconds before crash) |

> *Softmax tells you where the model ends up.  
> Semantic Velocity tells you whether it is losing control on the way.*

